# Anti-Patterns — Never Do These

## File & Language
- ❌ Never create `.ts` or `.tsx` files — this project is JavaScript + JSX only
- ❌ Never create `tsconfig.json` — use `jsconfig.json`
- ❌ Never use TypeScript syntax (`interface`, `type`, `: string`, `as`, generics)

---

## Imports
- ❌ Never use relative `../` imports — always use `@/` aliases
- ❌ Never import `react-router-dom` — use `next/link` and `next/navigation`
- ❌ Never import `Link` from react-router — import from `next/link`
- ❌ Never use `useNavigate` — use `useRouter` from `next/navigation`
- ❌ Never use `useParams` from react-router — use `params` prop on page component

---

## Components
- ❌ Never define data arrays inside a component file — put them in `src/lib/data/`
- ❌ Never put reusable components inside `src/app/` — use `src/components/` or `src/features/`
- ❌ Never use `<img>` — always use `next/image`
- ❌ Never use `<a href>` for internal links — always use `next/link`
- ❌ Never use array index as React `key` — use `id` or `slug`
- ❌ Never fetch data inside a Client Component with `useEffect` + `fetch` — fetch in Server Component and pass as props
- ❌ Never add `"use client"` to a file that doesn't need it

---

## Data & API
- ❌ Never remove `import 'server-only'` from any file in `src/lib/api/`
- ❌ Never use `process.env.SECRET_*` in a `"use client"` file or component
- ❌ Never commit `.env.local` — it must stay in `.gitignore`
- ❌ Never put icons or JSX inside `src/lib/data/` files — data files are pure JS

---

## Styling
- ❌ Never use inline `style={{ color: '#1d4ed8' }}` — use Tailwind classes
- ❌ Never create CSS module files (`.module.css`) — use Tailwind only
- ❌ Never use `@apply` in CSS except in `globals.css` for base resets
- ❌ Never hardcode hex colors in `className` — use CSS custom properties via `var()`

---

## Security
- ❌ Never expose secret keys in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables
- ❌ Never remove security headers from `next.config.js`
- ❌ Never return stack traces or full error objects in API route responses
- ❌ Never use unsanitized user content in `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`
- ❌ Never skip Zod validation in route handlers

---

## Architecture
- ❌ Never import a `features/` component from a different feature folder
  ```js
  // ❌ features/home/ importing from features/products/
  import ProductGrid from '@/features/products/ProductGrid'  // inside features/home/
  ```
  If a component is needed in two feature folders — **move it to `components/ui/`**

- ❌ Never put business logic inside `page.jsx` — pages only compose feature components and fetch data

- ❌ Never create a new top-level folder under `src/` without a clear reason — the current structure covers all needs:
  `app/`, `components/`, `features/`, `lib/`, `hooks/`, `config/`, `styles/`
